claim(address,uint256,address).details: Requirements:- The function initiator must have the claim role- {nft} must be supported by this contract- {tokenId} must be owned by this contract- {recipient} cannot be zero address- {recipient} must have the {IERC721ReceiverUpgradeable} interface if it is a smart contractEmits a {Transfer} and {Claim} event

params.recipient: The wallet address of the recipient
params.tokenId: The token id of the NFT

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

initialize(address).details: Requirements:- The Proxy contract have not been initialized beforeEmits an {Initialized} event

manageCollection(string,address,bool).details: Requirements:- The function initiator must have the default admin role- {nft} must not be zero addressEmits a {CollectionAdded}, {CollectionRemoved} or {CollectionAmended} event

params.name: The NFT collection name
params.supported: Indicate if the NFT collection is supported

onERC721Received(address,address,uint256.details: Interface that is necessary to receive asset via {safeTransfer} from ERC721 asset contract. Reverts if ERC721 asset contract is not supported by this contract

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

claimRole().notice: Return the bytes32 representation of the Claim role

getCollectionAddress(string).notice: Return the contract address of `name` if it is supported

initialize(address).notice: Initialize a Proxy contract and sets the address of the administrative and the CLAIM_ROLE slot

totalCollection().notice: Return the total number of NFT collections supported
